<div class="box" id="strategy-composition" name="strategy-composition">
  <div class="columns is-multiline is-centered">
    <div class="column is-half">
      <h2 class="title is-4 has-text-centered">Strategy Composition</h2>
      <dl>
        <dt class="title is-5">Strategy</dt>
        <dd class="content">The overall tactical plan at a commander level. A strategy will contain one or more objectives. Strategies can be simple, extremely complex, or anything in between.  </dd>

        <dt class="title is-5">Objective</dt>
        <dd class="content">The tactical plan at an operator level. Each operator will be assigned to a maximum of a single objective. Each objective may have as many operators as it requires.</dd>

        <dt class="title is-5">Stacked Objective</dt>
        <dd class="content">An Objective that is linked to one or more other objectives. Stacked objectives have an order, and each objective must be completed separately.</dd>

        <dt class="title is-5">Recipe</dt>
        <dd class="content">Outlines how an objective should be completed. Recipes are optional. An Objective without a mandatory recipe, allows the operator to complete the objective on his own terms. A Recipe may contains ingredients and or directions.
        </dd>

        <dt class="title is-5">Ingredient</dt>
        <dd class="content">A list pregame selections that are required for a recipe. This can include loadouts, respawns, and or characters.</dd>

        <dt class="title is-5">Direction</dt>
        <dd class="content">A single step of a recipe. Directions must be completed in order.</dd>
      </dl>
    </div>
    <div class="column is-half">
      <div class="mermaid">
        graph TD
            Strategy[fa:fa-chess Strategy]-->Objective[fa:fa-trophy Objective-A]
            Strategy[fa:fa-chess Strategy]-->Objective2[fa:fa-trophy Objective-B]
            Strategy[fa:fa-chess Strategy]-->Objective3[fa:fa-trophy Objective-C]
            Objective2-->Recipe[fa:fa-utensils RecipeA]
            Objective2-->Recipe2[fa:fa-utensils RecipeB]
            Objective2-->Recipe3[fa:fa-utensils RecipeC]
            Recipe2-->Directions[fa:fa-directions Directions]
            Recipe2-->Ingredients[fa:fa-cookie-bite Ingredients]
      </div>
    </div>
  </div>
</div>
<div class="columns is-centered">
  <div class="column is-half">
    <div name="objective-form-terms" id="objective-form-terms"  class="box">
      <h2 class="title is-4 has-text-centered">Objective Form Terms</h2>
      <dl>
        <dt class="title is-5">Minimum operators</dt>
        <dd class="content">When the app assigns objectives for each operator(at random), this value determines the minimum number of operators that will receive this objective.</dd>

        <dt class="title is-5">Maximum operators</dt>
        <dd class="content">When the app assigns objectives for each operator(at random), this value determines the maximum number of operators that will receive this objective.</dd>

        <dt class="title is-5">Priority level</dt>
        <dd class="content">When the app assigns objectives to each operator, this value helps reduce the randomness. Higher priority objectives will receive operators before lower priority ones. 10 is the lowest priority level, 1 is the highest priority level. This is especially useful when the total number of operators is less than the minimum number of operators required for the entire strategy.</dd>

        <dt class="title is-5">Stack objective</dt>
        <dd class="content">Stack up objectives one after the other. This allow operators to be assigned multiple objectives, but each objective must be complete separately.</dd>

        <dt class="title is-5">Dependency</dt>
        <dd class="content">Ensure the parent objective is completed before the children objectives can be started.</dd>

        <dt class="title is-5">Delay</dt>
        <dd class="content">Delay the start of an objective</dd>
      </dl>
    </div>
  </div>
</div>
